Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our
Harissa Beef and Bean Tacos in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

> Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!

== Bell Pepper Prep ==

If you don't have a #microwave{}, heat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark
7 for the tortillas.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

== Beef and Bean Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and chopped pepper. Fry until the
mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}) and drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%carton} in a
#sieve{}.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Mix in the @tomato puree{30%g} and
@harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for
~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, kidney beans, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Bring to the boil,
then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Tomato Prep ==

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1}(chopped into 1cm chunks).

== Tortillas ==

Pile the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) onto a #plate{}. Heat them
through in the microwave, 850W: ~{50%seconds} / 750W: ~{1%minute}, until warm
and soft.

If you're using the oven, lay the tortillas onto a #baking tray{} and place on
the middle shelf to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.
Remove from the heat.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}(or to taste) on each
tortilla.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and spoonfuls of the beef, pepper and bean
mixture - as much as you'd like.

Finish with the tomatoes and crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}(crumbled)
over the top.